  I also don't see us in some zombie state of being in which we obey the master.  What the hell kind of friend is that?  Didn't God create us to fullfill a role of companionship?  Do we force people or manipulate people to be our friends?  Do we demand that they submit to us?  When confronted with such an unknown issue, people tend to generalize in black and white.  Thats understandable, but through fear and insecurity through a lack of reconciliation with God, these fears become negative as we choose self-defense rather than confronting him.  Have you ever told a friend or even a potential friend(whom, in reality everyone is of that potential) to fuck off, eat shit, go to hell, or just die?  We all have.  Some friends forgive you, but some do not because they don't have the courage to overcome their pain or being stabbed in the back.  Then, if the friend doesn't seem to be forgiving of our actions, we have the choice of feeling guilty, feeling not wanted or some other insecurity which in turn develops into sadness or angry.  Most people get sick of sadness so they eventually evolve(if there is such a thing) into an anger approach.  Finding some reason to attack back, when now both are wrong.  Joe chose to use it as as excuse for higher ground whereas Jack shortly played the role of the hunchbacked scapegoat only to create a highground of his own to defy Joe.  Would a well-developed emotional and mental friend been like Joe or Jack?  I don't think so.  Life is fucking hard, theres no question about that, but I see a strong relationship as one where we are accepted and loved regardless of how often we check in or call or stay in touch with one another.  Thats just how I see it. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ucendan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Cendan</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0><